# Projection: PURRDF → pure gedcom. GENERATED by `purrdf regenerate` (mappings) from mapping-dsl/ — DO NOT EDIT.
# Lossy and directional by design; drops: standpoint/accordingTo provenance dropped; contested parentage emits coexisting rows; the relationship's standpoint/provenance drops; the child-to-family anchor survives; the traditional husband/wife terms emit ONLY in the clean documentary M+F configuration; any ambiguity, contestation, or absence degrades to symmetric spouseIn; gender identity is NEVER a source (SEX != GENDER); the couple relator's kind (marriage vs partnership) and validity period collapse to a bare Marriage node; partner roles stay symmetric (no husband/wife — SEX ≠ GENDER); the marriage event's participants, evidence and standpoint drop; only date + place survive on the Marriage node; the documentary sex-assigned-at-birth datum flattens to GEDCOM's SEX code ONLY when unambiguous; gender identity is NEVER a source (SEX != GENDER); any ambiguity degrades to 'U'; competing recorded values coexist in PURRDF (P9); the flat GEDCOM code degrades to 'U' rather than picking a winner; an intersex datum degrades to 'U' — GEDCOM's binary code cannot carry it and a forced M/F would misrepresent; an intersex-variation note marks the binary datum as insufficient; the code degrades to 'U' (the note itself is never exported).
PREFIX purrdf: <https://blackcatinformatics.ca/purrdf/>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX gedcom: <http://www.w3.org/2000/10/swap/pim/gedcom#>

CONSTRUCT {
    ?gparent gedcom:child ?gchild .
    ?gciChild gedcom:childIn ?gciFam .
    ?gfam a gedcom:Family .
    ?gfmFam gedcom:marriage ?gfmMarriage .
    ?ghwMarriage gedcom:husband ?ghwHim .
    ?ghwMarriage gedcom:wife ?ghwHer .
    ?gperson a gedcom:Individual .
    ?gmarriage a gedcom:Marriage .
    ?gp1 gedcom:spouseIn ?gmarriage .
    ?gp2 gedcom:spouseIn ?gmarriage .
    ?gmdMarriage gedcom:date ?gmdDate .
    ?gmdMarriage gedcom:place ?gmdPlace .
